# Who blocks ChatGPT?

The following {{ gptbot_rules_list|length }} news organizations have instructed [OpenAI's GPTBot](https://platform.openai.com/docs/gptbot) not scan their site, according to a daily survey of {{ "{:,.0f}".format(site_count) }} sites by The News Homepages Archive.

The artificial intelligence company [has suggested](https://www.theverge.com/2023/8/7/23823046/openai-data-scrape-block-ai) it will not train future editions of ChatGPT using sites that disallow access via the [`robots.txt`](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robots.txt) convention. Compliance with the standard is voluntary.

This page updates each day with the latest results.

